Description:
Stylish contemporary and light filled
This stylish four bedroom contemporary home offers an abundance of natural light throughout and cathedral ceilings through the kitchen/dining area, giving the sense of both space and luxury. The modern kitchen is simply stunning and is truly the hub of the home. Walk in pantry, soft close pot drawers throughout, Blanco stainless steel appliances and huge island bench with waterfall edges making it ideal for those that love to entertain. It opens up to both the dining and family room areas and then out to the outdoor entertaining area with blinds making it suitable to be used 365 days of the year. The second living area is intimate and ideal for a home theatre. The master bedroom is impressive and has a dressing room area with robe and ensuite with double sized shower, oversized vanity and separate shower. The remaining three bedrooms offer built in robes and share a three way bathroom. The bathroom has huge shower and bath with a separate toilet connected by an oversized vanity powder room. Climate throughout the home is controlled by reverse cycle ducted heating/cooling. The 20.3sq home was built by a quality builder in 2010 and has 5 k/W solar electricity and sprinklers in the lawns and gardens. For those that need accommodation for their big toys, this is sure to impress with rear yard access into the yard with double garage and 9m x 6m colorbond shed complete with mezzanine floor, keyless entry and three phase power. This home is sure to impress the most fastidious of buyers, so call to make an inspection today.

Family home on large block

The large master bedroom is located on the ground floor with an ensuite and walk in robe and can easily accommodate a king sized bed, whilst the remaining four bedrooms (all with built in robes) are located on the second floor with its own family bathroom. The kitchen has a huge amount of storage and bench space and comprises ceramic cooktop, electric wall oven and dishwasher and overlooks the family area that opens onto a large rear yard with paved court yard area with sail shades over. Climate throughout is controlled with the evaporative air conditioning to the second floor and two gas heaters to the ground floor. Call today for an inspection.

Description:
Oasis Village - Perfect community living
Positioned in Oasis Village this three bedroom home has been lovingly cared for and is fantastic value for money. It is compact in size making it perfect for the retiree ready to downsize. With open plan living the lounge room is generous in size and has the kitchen overlooking a separate meals area. The kitchen has pantry, microwave space and electric stove. All bedrooms have built in robes with the master bedroom also offering a ceiling fan. The bathroom has shower, toilet and vanity with a second toilet located off the separate laundry. There is heaps of storage in this home! The front verandah is wide enough across the front of the home to enjoy a cup of coffee in the sunshine. Climate throughout is controlled by ducted evaporative air conditioning and gas heater. Externally there is a double tandem carport, garden shed and low maintenance front and rear yards. Additional safety features throughout include handrails, grab rails and external non slip treads. Oasis Village gives retirees the freedom and independence they deserve and offers storage for caravans (subject to availability) and is conveniently located close to the public bus stop.

The laundry offers ample storage and bench space and has direct access outside. Externally there is a double garage with direct access into the home which is ideal for those that are security minded. Climate throughout is controlled by ducted evaporative air conditioning and gas ducted heating. There are additional upgrade features such as ducted vacuum system and is wired for future surround sound. This immaculately presented property will impress the most fastidious buyer and is only a short stroll to the CBD and is on its own title.
